						<div class="postbody">Well, I wouldn't ever want to write a GUI-program without a dialog editor (like the one found in Visual Studio). It sure helps.
<br />
<br />As for NES development... not sure.
<br />For symbolic debugging I wrote a command line tool to automatically convert cl65's VICE label files ("-g" switch on ca65, "-Ln xyz.lbl" on cl65) to the <em>romname.nes.ram.nl</em> format used by FCEUX's debugger.
<br />
<br />Automatic cycle counting sounds cool, but why not extend FCEUX or any other existing emulator to support it instead of completely re-inventing the wheel?</div>

